    • Constructor Detail

      • Telemetry

        public Telemetry(java.lang.String name)
        The object that represents a single telemetry value. Contains a name identifying the value, and the value itself. There are as many Telemetry objects for an App as there are qualities that can be displayed. For example, the Executive Services app has 35 potential Telemetry objects, with name instance variables such as "CmdCounter", "ErrCounter", "CFECoreChecksum".
        Parameters:
        name - What quality this represents
